@arjun4084346 The idea around manifest distcp is that the file diffing is outsourced from Gobblin, instead of Gobblin scanning files to copy and performing diffs, it is determined by an external system for efficiency gains. 

The recursiveCopyableDataset relies on the following function:
```
  @Override
  public Collection<? extends CopyEntity> getCopyableFiles(FileSystem targetFs, CopyConfiguration configuration)
      throws IOException {

    this.targetPath =
        new Path(configuration.getPublishDir(), PathUtils.relativizePath(this.rootPath, this.nonGlobSearchPath));

    Map<Path, FileStatus> filesInSource =
        createPathMap(getFilesAtPath(this.fs, this.rootPath, this.pathFilter), this.rootPath);
    Map<Path, FileStatus> filesInTarget =
        createPathMap(getFilesAtPath(targetFs, targetPath, this.pathFilter), targetPath);

    return getCopyableFilesImpl(configuration, filesInSource, filesInTarget, targetFs,
            nonGlobSearchPath, configuration.getPublishDir(), targetPath);
  }
```

And this scanning process at extremely large scale (30k+ file and hundreds of TB) is expensive and has a tendency to OOM due to not being streamed.

